.SH COMMON FLAGS
Many commands share the following flags:
.SS List Commands
.TP
.BI \-\-limit " int"
Maximum number of results to return (default 20).
.TP
.B \-\-all
Fetch all pages of results.
.TP
.BI \-\-search " string"
Filter results by search term.
.SS Get Commands
.TP
.BI \-\-watch " duration"
Poll for updates on an interval (e.g.,
.BR 5s ,
.BR 1m ).
.SS Destructive Commands
.TP
.B \-\-yes
Skip interactive confirmation prompt.
.SS Create/Update Commands
.TP
.BI \-\-from\-file " path"
Load request body from a JSON file. CLI flags override file values.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-input
Skip interactive prompts when fields are missing.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is stored in
.IR ~/.config/bunny/config.toml .
Run
.B bunny configure
to set it up interactively.
.PP
Example config file:
.PP
.RS
.nf
api_key = "your-api-key"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Configuration precedence (highest to lowest):
.IP 1. 4
Command-line flags
.IP 2. 4
Environment variables
.IP 3. 4
Config file
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B BUNNY_API_KEY
bunny.net API key.
.SH EXAMPLES
Configure the CLI:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ bunny configure
.fi
.RE
.PP
List pull zones as JSON:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ bunny pullzones list \-\-output json
.fi
.RE
.PP
Get a pull zone showing only name and origin URL:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ bunny pullzones get 12345 \-f Name,OriginUrl
.fi
.RE
.PP
Create a pull zone from a JSON file:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ bunny pullzones create \-\-from\-file pullzone.json
.fi
.RE
.PP
Purge cache for a pull zone:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ bunny pullzones purge 12345 \-\-yes
.fi
.RE
.PP
Upload a file to Edge Storage:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ bunny storage cp ./index.html my\-zone/www/index.html
.fi
.RE
.PP
Use jq to extract pull zone names:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ bunny pullzones list \-\-jq '.[].Name'
.fi
.RE
.PP
Deploy an edge script:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ bunny scripts code set 789 \-\-file worker.js
$ bunny scripts publish 789 \-\-note "v2.0 release"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Watch a pull zone for changes:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ bunny pullzones get 12345 \-\-watch 10s
.fi
.RE
.PP
Generate Zsh completions:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ bunny completion zsh > "${fpath[1]}/_bunny"
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
General error (API error, invalid input, network failure).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/bunny/config.toml
CLI configuration file (dir 0700, file 0600).
